==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rhodium
<hw>Rho"di*um</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>"ro`don</grk> the rose. So called from the rose-red color of
certain of its solutions. See <er>Rhododendron</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A rare element of the light platinum group. It
is found in platinum ores, and obtained free as a white inert metal
which it is very difficult to fuse. Symbol Rh. Atomic weight 104.1.
Specific gravity 12.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rhodizonic</ent>⟦br⟧
